00001 /******************************************************************************************************************************
00002  * NOTE:  For any given IR class, please keep all its parts as close together as possible.  Its bad enough that we're
00003  *        defining classes in a non-C-like language -- and it's painful when a definition is scattered all over this file. We
00004  *        already have four places to look to get the definition of an IR class:
00005  *              (1) here, in this source file, built with ROSETTA functions
00006  *              (2) additional declarations between HEADER_* markers in ../Grammar/BinaryInstruction.code (which we can't
00007  *                  even parse as a C++ file, making IDEs useless there).
00008  *              (3) function definitions between SOURCE_* markers in ../Grammar/BinaryInstruction.code, which for some
00009  *                  reason are not next to the corresponding HEADER_ markers.  Please migrate these definitions to *.C files
00010  *                  whenever you have an opportunity, so that IDEs can see the definitions.
00011  *              (4) Doxygen documentation in ../../../docs/testDoxygen directory since doxygen can't parse the IR classes
00012  *                  from this source file.  Documented entities are marked with a "DOXYGEN" comment here to make it more
00013  *                  obvious when documentation is present.
00014  *
00015  * NOTE:  First part of the file is for classes describing instructions.  Middle part is for classes describing binary
00016  *        containers (organized by container type: ELF, DOS, PE, ...)  Last part is the base classes.  Unlike C++, the classes
00017  *        defined in this file need to be defined from the most specific (derived classes) to the most general (base class).
00018  *
00019  * NOTE:  Please use three blank lines between IR node definitions to help make this file more readable.  Unless those IR
00020  *        nodes are so closely related to one another that it's better to keep them close.
00021  *-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
